	   <tr><td colspan=2>The problem with the IG's inside perma resisting everything is because you are only allowed to cast on them if you are in melee range.  If you are outside of Melee range, all of your spells will be resisted, if you are inside, they will take effect and you are of course open for attack.<br><br>This applies for damage spells, , since I am a Wizard I have little experience with the other spell lines, so debuffs and such may work outside of melee range.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
