<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100339380082288></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100339380082288><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=/search.shtml?id=660&mid=100339380082288>RE: need 2 know for a quest:</a> <a id=fs8 href=/search.shtml?id=660&mid=100339380082288#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=97944><span id= >harrije</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 18th 4:30 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This one demands a little explanation.<br><br>Prior to the expansions, there were no frost giants in the game. One of the magician Solusek Ro quests called for 'frost giant toes,' and since the Everfrost/Permafrost giants were the frostiest in the game, everyone knew that 'ice giant toes' would work just fine.<br><br>However, on the continent of Velious, there *are* now frost giants, and they do drop toes (frost giant toes) which are used for some Velious quests.<br><br>Because of the confusion, Vera in the Temple of Solusek Ro now asks for 'ice giant toes' when doing the Stein of Ulissa quest. And yes, these giants do drop the requisite toes for that quest.<br><br>If, however, you are doing the Coldain Prayer Shawl quest in Thurgadin, you will need the Frost Giant Toes which dropped off...you guessed it, frost giants, found in the first few zones of Velious.<br><br>At level 7, your best bet for getting a set of toes is to make the trip to Everfrost (might want to wait a level and use invisibility for the trip) and politely ask a high level if you may loot a set of toes. In all likelihood, they will agree. You can probably also find a set on one of the Halas vendors for roughly 10pp.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
