<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9944443715203></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9944443715203><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=/search.shtml?id=660&mid=9944443715203>Ice Giants</a> <a id=fs8 href=/search.shtml?id=660&mid=9944443715203#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=20 width=20></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Jul 6th 2:32 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Okay here's the lowdown about the Ice giants and the Seafury Cyclops in OOT.<br><br>Ice giants (ones on the entrance to permafrost) <br>Max dam: 105 (avg 80s)<br>HP: 3000-3500hp<br>Loot: <br>Common: approx 40pp (random amount), words/runes<br>Rare: Block of permafrost<br><br>Seafury Cyclops (on Seafury Island in OOT)<br>Max dam: 96 (avg 70s)<br>HP: 3500-3800hp<br>Loot: <br>Common: approx 5pp (random amount), words/runes<br>Rare: random gem (sapphire, fire emerald, Fire opal), mithril armlet<br><br>These con green with a few blue ones for a lvl 52 mage. As you can see the Ice giants hit harder, have a bit less hp and has good PP for loot, while the Seafury cyclops has a bit more hp, hit only for around 96 and has few PP for loot (due to the Verant nerf bat) but infrequently it drops gems which are lighter/stackable and sell for a pretty penny (sapphires sell for around 95pp to vendors).<br><br>Personally I prefer killing the Seafuries over the ice giants.<br><br>P.S. I don't recommend using Fire pet when solo fighting the ice giants or it will be slaughtered in short order. Even my lvl 51 earth pet (Vocerate: Earth) got pounded to less than 1/5th of its life and would probably die if i did not do a few timely 810 damage nukes (Lava bolt).<br><br>Alladdim Allibabua<br>52 Elementalist, Bertoxxulous<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
